{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:58,010", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task2: ```json\n{\n  \"resume_job_match_analysis_algorithm\": {\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"description\": \"Algorithm to match a candidate's resume against a job description, providing a match score and identifying key alignment points.\",\n    \"component_weights\": {\n      \"experience\": 0.4,\n      \"skills\": 0.3,\n      \"education\": 0.15,\n      \"certifications\": 0.1,\n      \"projects\": 0.05\n    },\n    \"keyword_extraction\": {\n      \"method\": \"SpaCy NLP + Custom Dictionary\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"1. Input text: Job description and resume sections.\",\n        \"2. Preprocessing: Lowercasing, punctuation removal, stop word removal using SpaCy.\",\n        \"3. Lemmatization: Reduce words to their base form using SpaCy.\",\n        \"4. Named Entity Recognition (NER): Identify key entities (e.g., skills, companies, job titles) using SpaCy's NER.\",\n        \"5. Custom Dictionary Augmentation: Enrich extracted keywords with synonyms and related terms from a domain-specific dictionary (e.g., technical skills, HR terms).\",\n        \"6. TF-IDF Scoring: Calculate TF-IDF scores for each term in both the job description and resume sections.\",\n        \"7. Keyword Selection: Select top N keywords based on TF-IDF scores and relevance (e.g., filtering out overly generic terms).\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"similarity_calculation\": {\n      \"experience\": {\n        \"method\": \"Cosine Similarity on Keyword Vectors\",\n        \"description\": \"Calculate the cosine similarity between keyword vectors extracted from the 'experience' sections of the job description and resume.  Each experience entry is treated as a document.\",\n        \"details\": \"Keywords are weighted by TF-IDF.  A minimum overlap threshold (e.g., 0.1) can be applied to avoid matching unrelated experiences.\",\n        \"weight\": 1.0\n      },\n      \"skills\": {\n        \"method\": \"Jaccard Similarity with Synonym Expansion\",\n        \"description\": \"Calculate the Jaccard similarity (intersection over union) between skill sets listed in the job description and resume. Synonym expansion is performed using WordNet or a custom thesaurus.\",\n        \"details\": \"Skills are normalized (e.g., 'Java' and 'Java Programming' are considered the same).  Skills are stemmed before comparison.\",\n        \"weight\": 1.0\n      },\n      \"education\": {\n        \"method\": \"String Similarity and Semantic Matching\",\n        \"description\": \"Match education entries based on degree name, major, and institution. A combination of string similarity (Levenshtein distance) and semantic matching (using word embeddings) is used.\",\n        \"details\": \"Higher weight is given to exact matches of degree names. Semantic matching is used to identify related majors (e.g., 'Computer Science' and 'Software Engineering').\",\n        \"weight\": 0.8\n      },\n      \"certifications\": {\n        \"method\": \"Exact and Fuzzy String Matching\",\n        \"description\": \"Identify matching certifications using both exact and fuzzy string matching (e.g., using the FuzzyWuzzy library).\",\n        \"details\": \"Partial matches (e.g., a slightly different certification name) receive a lower score.  Certifications from reputable organizations receive a higher weight.\",\n        \"weight\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"projects\": {\n        \"method\": \"Keyword Overlap and Description Similarity\",\n        \"description\": \"Analyzes project descriptions in the resume for keyword overlap with the job description's required skills and responsibilities.  Cosine similarity is used to compare project descriptions.\",\n        \"details\": \"Projects demonstrating relevant experience (e.g., AI projects for an AI role) are weighted higher.\",\n         \"weight\": 0.7\n      }\n    },\n    \"scoring\": {\n      \"detailed\": {\n        \"experience\": \"score_experience = similarity_experience * component_weights['experience']\",\n        \"skills\": \"score_skills = similarity_skills * component_weights['skills']\",\n        \"education\": \"score_education = similarity_education * component_weights['education']\",\n        \"certifications\": \"score_certifications = similarity_certifications * component_weights['certifications']\",\n        \"projects\": \"score_projects = similarity_projects * component_weights['projects']\"\n      },\n      \"aggregate\": {\n        \"formula\": \"match_score = score_experience + score_skills + score_education + score_certifications + score_projects\",\n        \"normalization\": \"match_score = min(1.0, match_score)  # Ensure match_score is between 0.0 and 1.0\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"match_thresholds\": {\n      \"excellent\": 0.85,\n      \"good\": 0.7,\n      \"average\": 0.5,\n      \"poor\": 0.3\n    },\n    \"output_structure\": {\n      \"match_score\": \"Float between 0.0 and 1.0 indicating overall match strength.\",\n      \"key_alignment_points\": {\n        \"experience\": [\"List of top matched experience keywords and corresponding job responsibilities.\"],\n        \"skills\": [\"List of matched skill keywords and indication of proficiency level (if available).\"],\n        \"education\": [\"Matched degree names, majors, and institutions. Indication of relevance to the job.\"],\n        \"certifications\": [\"Matched certification names and issuing organizations.\"],\n        \"projects\": [\"List of projects that demonstrate key skills or experience related to the job description.\"]\n      },\n      \"detailed_analysis\": {\n        \"experience_match\": {\n          \"score\": \"Float representing the experience match score.\",\n          \"matched_keywords\": [\"List of keywords matched in the experience section.\"],\n          \"unmatched_keywords\": [\"List of keywords from the job description not found in the experience section.\"]\n        },\n        \"skills_match\": {\n          \"score\": \"Float representing the skills match score.\",\n          \"matched_keywords\": [\"List of skills matched.\"],\n          \"unmatched_keywords\": [\"List of required skills not found.\"]\n        },\n        \"education_match\": {\n          \"score\": \"Float representing the education match score.\",\n          \"matched_keywords\": [\"List of matched education details.\"],\n          \"unmatched_keywords\": [\"List of required education details not found.\"]\n        },\n        \"certifications_match\": {\n          \"score\": \"Float representing the certifications match score.\",\n          \"matched_keywords\": [\"List of matched certifications.\"],\n          \"unmatched_keywords\": [\"List of required certifications not found.\"]\n        },\n         \"projects_match\": {\n          \"score\": \"Float representing the projects match score.\",\n          \"matched_keywords\": [\"List of keywords matched in the projects section.\"],\n          \"unmatched_keywords\": [\"List of keywords from the job description not found in the projects section.\"]\n        },\n        \"overall_summary\": \"String summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses based on the resume-job match. Highlights key areas of alignment and gaps.\"\n      },\n      \"recommendation\": \"String suggesting a course of action based on the match_score and detailed analysis (e.g., 'Highly recommended for interview', 'Consider for further evaluation', 'Not a strong match').\"\n    },\n    \"dependencies\": [\n      \"SpaCy NLP library\",\n      \"WordNet or a custom thesaurus for synonym expansion\",\n      \"FuzzyWuzzy library for fuzzy string matching\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:58,010", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task3: ```python\nimport json\nimport random\n\nclass InterviewEngine:\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initializes the InterviewEngine with job description and candidate profile.\n\n        Args:\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile_json\n        self.technical_questions = self.load_questions(\"technical\")\n        self.behavioral_questions = self.load_questions(\"behavioral\")\n        self.follow_up_questions = self.load_questions(\"follow_up\") # Load follow-up questions\n\n    def load_questions(self, question_type=\"technical\"):\n          \"\"\"\n          Loads questions from JSON files based on question type.\n\n          Args:\n              question_type (str): Type of questions to load (\"technical\", \"behavioral\", \"follow_up\").\n\n          Returns:\n              list: A list of dictionaries, each representing a question.\n          \"\"\"\n          try:\n              with open(f\"questions_{question_type}.json\", \"r\") as f:\n                  questions = json.load(f)\n              return questions\n          except FileNotFoundError:\n              print(f\"Error: questions_{question_type}.json not found.  Returning empty list.\")\n              return []\n\n    def generate_initial_question(self, question_type=\"technical\"):\n        \"\"\"\n        Generates an initial technical or behavioral question.\n\n        Args:\n            question_type (str): \"technical\" or \"behavioral\".\n\n        Returns:\n            dict: A question dictionary.\n        \"\"\"\n        if question_type == \"technical\":\n            questions = self.technical_questions\n        elif question_type == \"behavioral\":\n            questions = self.behavioral_questions\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(\"Invalid question type.  Must be 'technical' or 'behavioral'.\")\n\n        if not questions:\n            return {\"question\": \"No questions available for this type.\"}\n\n        return random.choice(questions)\n\n    def generate_follow_up_question(self, candidate_answer):\n        \"\"\"\n        Generates a follow-up question based on the candidate's answer.  This is a simplified\n        implementation that randomly selects a follow-up question.  A more sophisticated\n        implementation would analyze the candidate's answer and select a follow-up question\n        that is relevant to the answer.\n\n        Args:\n            candidate_answer (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\n\n        Returns:\n            dict: A follow-up question dictionary.\n        \"\"\"\n        if not self.follow_up_questions:\n            return {\"question\": \"No follow-up questions available.\"}\n\n        return random.choice(self.follow_up_questions)\n\n    def conduct_interview(self, num_technical_questions=3, num_behavioral_questions=2):\n        \"\"\"\n        Conducts a dynamic interview with technical and behavioral questions.\n\n        Args:\n            num_technical_questions (int): Number of technical questions to ask.\n            num_behavioral_questions (int): Number of behavioral questions to ask.\n\n        Returns:\n            list: A list of dictionaries, each containing a question, the candidate's answer, and any follow-up questions/answers.\n        \"\"\"\n        interview_transcript = []\n\n        # Technical Questions\n        for _ in range(num_technical_questions):\n            question_data = self.generate_initial_question(question_type=\"technical\")\n            question = question_data[\"question\"]\n            print(f\"Technical Question: {question}\")\n            candidate_answer = input(\"Your Answer: \")  # Simulate candidate answering\n            interview_transcript.append({\"question\": question, \"answer\": candidate_answer, \"follow_ups\": []})\n\n            # Generate and ask a follow-up question\n            follow_up_data = self.generate_follow_up_question(candidate_answer)\n            follow_up_question = follow_up_data[\"question\"]\n            print(f\"Follow-up: {follow_up_question}\")\n            follow_up_answer = input(\"Your Answer: \") # Simulate candidate answering\n            interview_transcript[-1][\"follow_ups\"].append({\"question\": follow_up_question, \"answer\": follow_up_answer})\n\n\n        # Behavioral Questions\n        for _ in range(num_behavioral_questions):\n            question_data = self.generate_initial_question(question_type=\"behavioral\")\n            question = question_data[\"question\"]\n            print(f\"Behavioral Question: {question}\")\n            candidate_answer = input(\"Your Answer: \")  # Simulate candidate answering\n            interview_transcript.append({\"question\": question, \"answer\": candidate_answer, \"follow_ups\": []})\n\n            # Generate and ask a follow-up question\n            follow_up_data = self.generate_follow_up_question(candidate_answer)\n            follow_up_question = follow_up_data[\"question\"]\n            print(f\"Follow-up: {follow_up_question}\")\n            follow_up_answer = input(\"Your Answer: \") # Simulate candidate answering\n            interview_transcript[-1][\"follow_ups\"].append({\"question\": follow_up_question, \"answer\": follow_up_answer})\n\n\n        return interview_transcript\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Sample Usage (replace with actual JSON data)\n    job_description_data = {\n      \"job_title\": \"Software Engineer\",\n      \"skills\": {\n        \"technical\": [\"Python\", \"Data Analysis\"]\n      }\n    }\n    candidate_profile_data = {\n      \"candidate_profile\": {\n        \"skills\": [\"Python\", \"Machine Learning\"]\n      }\n    }\n\n    # Create dummy question files\n    with open(\"questions_technical.json\", \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump([{\"question\": \"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the time complexity of a dictionary lookup?\"}], f)\n    with open(\"questions_behavioral.json\", \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump([{\"question\": \"Tell me about a time you failed.\"}, {\"question\": \"Describe a time you had to work with a difficult team member.\"}], f)\n    with open(\"questions_follow_up.json\", \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump([{\"question\": \"Can you elaborate on that?\"}, {\"question\": \"What were the key takeaways?\"}], f)\n\n\n\n    engine = InterviewEngine(job_description_data, candidate_profile_data)\n    interview_transcript = engine.conduct_interview()\n\n    print(\"\\nInterview Transcript:\")\n    print(json.dumps(interview_transcript, indent=4))\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:58,010", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task4: ```python\nimport json\n\nclass AnswerEvaluator:\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initializes the AnswerEvaluator with job description and candidate profile.\n\n        Args:\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile_json\n\n    def evaluate_answer(self, question, answer, question_type=\"technical\"):\n        \"\"\"\n        Evaluates a candidate's answer based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\n\n        Args:\n            question (str): The question asked.\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\n            question_type (str): \"technical\" or \"behavioral\".\n\n        Returns:\n            dict: A dictionary containing evaluation scores and feedback.\n        \"\"\"\n        evaluation = {\n            \"relevance\": self.evaluate_relevance(question, answer),\n            \"depth\": self.evaluate_depth(answer),\n            \"confidence\": self.evaluate_confidence(answer),\n        }\n\n        if question_type == \"technical\":\n            evaluation[\"technical_accuracy\"] = self.evaluate_technical_accuracy(question, answer)\n        else:\n            evaluation[\"technical_accuracy\"] = None\n\n        evaluation[\"overall_score\"] = self.calculate_overall_score(evaluation)\n        evaluation[\"feedback\"] = self.generate_feedback(evaluation, question_type)\n\n        return evaluation\n\n    def evaluate_relevance(self, question, answer):\n        \"\"\"\n        Evaluates the relevance of the answer to the question.\n\n        Args:\n            question (str): The question asked.\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\n\n        Returns:\n            int: Relevance score (0-5).\n        \"\"\"\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\n        if not answer:\n            return 0  # No answer provided\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\n        common_keywords = set(keywords_in_question) & set(keywords_in_answer)\n        score = min(5, len(common_keywords)) # Cap the score at 5\n        return score\n\n    def evaluate_depth(self, answer):\n        \"\"\"\n        Evaluates the depth of the answer.\n\n        Args:\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\n\n        Returns:\n            int: Depth score (0-5).\n        \"\"\"\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\n        length = len(answer.split())\n        if length < 10:\n            return 1\n        elif length < 50:\n            return 3\n        else:\n            return 5\n\n    def evaluate_confidence(self, answer):\n        \"\"\"\n        Evaluates the confidence conveyed in the answer.\n\n        Args:\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\n\n        Returns:\n            int: Confidence score (0-5).\n        \"\"\"\n        # Placeholder implementation - analyze tone, certainty words, etc.\n        # Example: Check for hesitant language (\"I think\", \"maybe\", \"I'm not sure\")\n        hesitation_words = [\"I think\", \"maybe\", \"I'm not sure\", \"I believe\"]\n        hesitation_count = sum([answer.lower().count(word) for word in hesitation_words])\n\n        if hesitation_count > 2:\n          return 2\n        elif hesitation_count > 0:\n            return 3\n        else:\n            return 5\n\n    def evaluate_technical_accuracy(self, question, answer):\n        \"\"\"\n        Evaluates the technical accuracy of the answer.\n\n        Args:\n            question (str): The technical question asked.\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\n\n        Returns:\n            int: Technical accuracy score (0-5).\n        \"\"\"\n        # Placeholder implementation - requires domain-specific knowledge\n        # This is a very basic example.  In a real application, this would\n        # involve more sophisticated techniques such as:\n        #   - Knowledge graphs\n        #   - Code execution and testing\n        #   - Comparison to expected answers\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\n\n        # Check for specific keywords related to common technical concepts\n        if \"time complexity\" in question.lower() and (\"O(n)\" in answer or \"O(1)\" in answer):\n            return 5\n        elif \"linked list\" in question.lower() and \"nodes\" in answer.lower() and \"pointers\" in answer.lower():\n            return 4\n        else:\n            return 3 # Default score if no specific keywords are found\n\n    def calculate_overall_score(self, evaluation):\n        \"\"\"\n        Calculates the overall score based on individual evaluation metrics.\n\n        Args:\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\n\n        Returns:\n            float: Overall score (0-5).\n        \"\"\"\n        total_score = evaluation[\"relevance\"] + evaluation[\"depth\"] + evaluation[\"confidence\"]\n        if evaluation[\"technical_accuracy\"] is not None:\n            total_score += evaluation[\"technical_accuracy\"]\n            num_metrics = 4\n        else:\n            num_metrics = 3\n\n        return total_score / num_metrics\n\n    def generate_feedback(self, evaluation, question_type):\n        \"\"\"\n        Generates feedback based on the evaluation scores.\n\n        Args:\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\n            question_type (str): \"technical\" or \"behavioral\".\n\n        Returns:\n            str: Feedback string.\n        \"\"\"\n        feedback = \"\"\n        if evaluation[\"relevance\"] < 3:\n            feedback += \"The answer could be more relevant to the question. \"\n        if evaluation[\"depth\"] < 3:\n            feedback += \"The answer could be more in-depth. \"\n        if evaluation[\"confidence\"] < 3:\n            feedback += \"The answer could be delivered with more confidence. \"\n        if question_type == \"technical\" and evaluation[\"technical_accuracy\"] < 3:\n            feedback += \"The technical accuracy of the answer could be improved. \"\n\n        if not feedback:\n            feedback = \"The answer was well-received.\"\n\n        return feedback\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Sample Usage\n    job_description_data = {\n        \"job_title\": \"Software Engineer\",\n        \"skills\": {\n            \"technical\": [\"Python\", \"Data Analysis\"]\n        }\n    }\n    candidate_profile_data = {\n        \"candidate_profile\": {\n            \"skills\": [\"Python\", \"Machine Learning\"]\n        }\n    }\n\n    evaluator = AnswerEvaluator(job_description_data, candidate_profile_data)\n\n    technical_question = \"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\"\n    technical_answer = \"Lists are mutable, while tuples are immutable.\"\n    technical_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(technical_question, technical_answer, \"technical\")\n    print(\"Technical Question Evaluation:\", technical_evaluation)\n\n    behavioral_question = \"Tell me about a time you failed.\"\n    behavioral_answer = \"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the workload.\"\n    behavioral_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(behavioral_question, behavioral_answer, \"behavioral\")\n    print(\"Behavioral Question Evaluation:\", behavioral_evaluation)\n```"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:58,010", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task5: ```python\nclass ScoringAggregator:\n    \"\"\"\n    Aggregates scores from resume matching, technical assessments, and behavioral assessments\n    to produce a final candidate score and evaluation.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, resume_job_match_weight=0.3, technical_assessment_weight=0.4, behavioral_assessment_weight=0.3):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initializes the ScoringAggregator with weights for each assessment category.\n\n        Args:\n            resume_job_match_weight (float): Weight for the resume-job match score (default: 0.3).\n            technical_assessment_weight (float): Weight for the technical assessment score (default: 0.4).\n            behavioral_assessment_weight (float): Weight for the behavioral assessment score (default: 0.3).\n        \"\"\"\n        if sum([resume_job_match_weight, technical_assessment_weight, behavioral_assessment_weight]) != 1.0:\n            raise ValueError(\"The sum of the weights must equal 1.0\")\n\n        self.resume_job_match_weight = resume_job_match_weight\n        self.technical_assessment_weight = technical_assessment_weight\n        self.behavioral_assessment_weight = behavioral_assessment_weight\n\n    def aggregate_scores(self, resume_job_match_score, technical_assessment_scores, behavioral_assessment_scores):\n        \"\"\"\n        Aggregates scores from different assessment categories into a final score.\n\n        Args:\n            resume_job_match_score (float): The resume-job match score (0.0 to 1.0).\n            technical_assessment_scores (list of floats): A list of technical assessment scores (0.0 to 5.0).\n            behavioral_assessment_scores (list of floats): A list of behavioral assessment scores (0.0 to 5.0).\n\n        Returns:\n            dict: A dictionary containing the aggregated score and individual component scores.\n        \"\"\"\n\n        # Calculate the average technical assessment score\n        if technical_assessment_scores:\n            avg_technical_score = sum(technical_assessment_scores) / len(technical_assessment_scores)\n        else:\n            avg_technical_score = 0.0\n\n        # Calculate the average behavioral assessment score\n        if behavioral_assessment_scores:\n            avg_behavioral_score = sum(behavioral_assessment_scores) / len(behavioral_assessment_scores)\n        else:\n            avg_behavioral_score = 0.0\n\n        # Normalize the technical and behavioral scores to be between 0.0 and 1.0\n        normalized_technical_score = avg_technical_score / 5.0 if avg_technical_score > 0 else 0.0\n        normalized_behavioral_score = avg_behavioral_score / 5.0 if avg_behavioral_score > 0 else 0.0\n\n        # Calculate the weighted final score\n        final_score = (\n            self.resume_job_match_weight * resume_job_match_score +\n            self.technical_assessment_weight * normalized_technical_score +\n            self.behavioral_assessment_weight * normalized_behavioral_score\n        )\n\n        return {\n            \"final_score\": final_score,\n            \"resume_job_match_score\": resume_job_match_score,\n            \"avg_technical_score\": avg_technical_score,\n            \"avg_behavioral_score\": avg_behavioral_score,\n            \"weighted_resume_score\": self.resume_job_match_weight * resume_job_match_score,\n            \"weighted_technical_score\": self.technical_assessment_weight * normalized_technical_score,\n            \"weighted_behavioral_score\": self.behavioral_assessment_weight * normalized_behavioral_score,\n        }\n\n    def generate_recommendation(self, final_score, thresholds=None):\n        \"\"\"\n        Generates a recommendation based on the final score.\n\n        Args:\n            final_score (float): The final aggregated score.\n            thresholds (dict, optional): A dictionary containing thresholds for different recommendation levels.\n                                          Defaults to {\"strong_yes\": 0.85, \"yes\": 0.7, \"maybe\": 0.5, \"no\": 0.3}.\n\n        Returns:\n            str: A recommendation string.\n        \"\"\"\n        if thresholds is None:\n            thresholds = {\"strong_yes\": 0.85, \"yes\": 0.7, \"maybe\": 0.5, \"no\": 0.3}\n\n        if final_score >= thresholds[\"strong_yes\"]:\n            return \"Strongly Recommend for Hire\"\n        elif final_score >= thresholds[\"yes\"]:\n            return \"Recommend for Hire\"\n        elif final_score >= thresholds[\"maybe\"]:\n            return \"Consider for Further Evaluation\"\n        else:\n            return \"Not Recommended for Hire\"\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Example Usage\n    aggregator = ScoringAggregator(resume_job_match_weight=0.3, technical_assessment_weight=0.4, behavioral_assessment_weight=0.3)\n\n    # Sample scores\n    resume_match_score = 0.8\n    technical_scores = [4.0, 4.5, 3.5]\n    behavioral_scores = [3.0, 4.0, 5.0]\n\n    # Aggregate the scores\n    aggregated_results = aggregator.aggregate_scores(resume_match_score, technical_scores, behavioral_scores)\n    print(\"Aggregated Results:\", aggregated_results)\n\n    # Generate a recommendation\n    recommendation = aggregator.generate_recommendation(aggregated_results[\"final_score\"])\n    print(\"Recommendation:\", recommendation)\n```\n"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:58,010", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "flow", "function": "run_async", "line": 205, "message": " - task6: ```python\ndef generate_interview_invitation_email(candidate_name, interview_date, interview_time, interviewer_name, meeting_link, job_title, company_name):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generates an email invitation for an interview.\n\n    Args:\n        candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n        interview_date (str): The date of the interview (e.g., \"October 26, 2023\").\n        interview_time (str): The time of the interview (e.g., \"10:00 AM PST\").\n        interviewer_name (str): The name of the interviewer.\n        meeting_link (str): The link to the online meeting.\n        job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is interviewing for.\n        company_name (str): The name of the company.\n\n    Returns:\n        str: The generated email invitation.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    subject = f\"Interview Invitation: {job_title} at {company_name}\"\n    body = f\"\"\"\nDear {candidate_name},\n\nWe are pleased to invite you to interview for the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\n\nYour interview is scheduled for:\n\nDate: {interview_date}\nTime: {interview_time}\nInterviewer: {interviewer_name}\nMeeting Link: {meeting_link}\n\nPlease join the meeting at the scheduled time by clicking on the link above.\n\nWe look forward to speaking with you!\n\nSincerely,\n\nThe {company_name} Recruiting Team\n\"\"\"\n    return subject, body\n\n\ndef generate_interview_followup_email(candidate_name, interviewer_name, job_title, company_name):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generates a follow-up email after an interview.\n\n    Args:\n        candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n        interviewer_name (str): The name of the interviewer.\n        job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate interviewed for.\n        company_name (str): The name of the company.\n\n    Returns:\n        str: The generated follow-up email.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    subject = f\"Thank you for interviewing with {company_name}\"\n    body = f\"\"\"\nDear {candidate_name},\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with {interviewer_name} for the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\n\nWe appreciate you sharing your experience and qualifications with us.\n\nWe are currently reviewing all candidates and will be in touch with you regarding the next steps in the hiring process.\n\nThank you again for your interest in {company_name}.\n\nSincerely,\n\nThe {company_name} Recruiting Team\n\"\"\"\n    return subject, body\n\n\ndef generate_rejection_email(candidate_name, job_title, company_name):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generates a rejection email after an interview.\n\n    Args:\n        candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n        job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate interviewed for.\n        company_name (str): The name of the company.\n\n    Returns:\n        str: The generated rejection email.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    subject = f\"Update on your application for {job_title} at {company_name}\"\n    body = f\"\"\"\nDear {candidate_name},\n\nThank you for your interest in the {job_title} position at {company_name}. We appreciate you taking the time to interview with our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with other candidates whose qualifications and experience more closely align with the requirements of this role.\n\nThis was a difficult decision, as we were impressed with many aspects of your background. We encourage you to apply for other positions at {company_name} that may be a good fit for your skills and experience.\n\nWe wish you the best of luck in your job search.\n\nSincerely,\n\nThe {company_name} Recruiting Team\n\"\"\"\n    return subject, body\n\n\ndef generate_offer_email(candidate_name, job_title, company_name, salary, start_date, benefits_summary):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generates an offer email for a candidate.\n\n    Args:\n        candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\n        job_title (str): The title of the job being offered.\n        company_name (str): The name of the company.\n        salary (str): The salary being offered (e.g., \"$100,000 per year\").\n        start_date (str): The start date of the job (e.g., \"November 1, 2023\").\n        benefits_summary (str): A brief summary of the benefits offered.\n\n    Returns:\n        str: The generated offer email.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    subject = f\"Job Offer: {job_title} at {company_name}\"\n    body = f\"\"\"\nDear {candidate_name},\n\nWe are delighted to offer you the position of {job_title} at {company_name}!\n\nWe were very impressed with your qualifications and experience during the interview process, and we believe you would be a valuable asset to our team.\n\nHere are the details of our offer:\n\nJob Title: {job_title}\nSalary: {salary}\nStart Date: {start_date}\nBenefits: {benefits_summary}\n\nWe have attached a formal offer letter with more details about the position and benefits. Please review it carefully and let us know if you have any questions.\n\nWe are excited about the possibility of you joining our team! Please let us know your decision by [Date].\n\nSincerely,\n\nThe {company_name} Recruiting Team\n\"\"\"\n    return subject, body\n```"}
